    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Monoctonia japonica Rakhshani & Tomanović, sp. n., female—A. Head; B. Antenna; C. Maxillary and labial palpomeres; D. Propodeum; E. Petiole; F. Fore wing; G. Hind wing; H. Genitalia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/242670/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.242672>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cocoons of Monoctonia species, A. Forda marginata parasitized by Monoctonia pistaciaecola; B. Pemphigus matsumurai parasitized by Monoctonia japonica; C and D. Pemphigus spyrothecae parasitized by Monoctonia vesicarii; E. Emergence of adult parasitoid, M. vesicarii from the cocoons." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/242672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

